<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="533" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/9696</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Netherland Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">De Beaufort</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-29">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge with
                                thanks the receipt of your note of April 23, 1918, with respect to
                                the decision of the Royal Government to send a convoy to the Dutch
                                East Indies in June next, for the purpose of relieving the personnel
                                of the Ministry, transferring <pb facs="0650" n="1484" xml:id="pg_1484"/> Government officials and their families and
                                to carry military supplies for the colonial army.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>